items.title: Man found dead, ending manhunt after woman stabbed outside Melbourne home
items.standfirst: A man has been found dead hours after a woman was stabbed in front of her home in Melbourne's east.
items.content: A young man has been found dead in regional Victoria, ending a manhunt that began after a young woman was stabbed outside a home in Melbourne's east early this morning.The 18-year-old woman was returning from a night out with friends when she was allegedly confronted by a man and stabbed about 1am outside a house on Miller Grove in Kew, according to police.The woman was taken to hospital with what was initially believed to be life-threatening injuries. READ MORE: Police investigating if driver error to blame for train crash that killed two READ MORE: Surfer's chilling warning before Manly attackShe is now in a stable condition and recovering in hospital.Soon after the attack, police began searching for an 18-year-old Camberwell man.About 6.15am, a Triple Zero call reported a body of a man in Antwerp, 356 kilometres north-west of Melbourne. The death of the man is not being treated as suspicious and a report will be prepared for the coroner.Police are not looking for anyone else in relation to the stabbing in Kew.Lifeline 13 11 14DOWNLOAD THE 9NEWS APP: Stay across all the latest in breaking news, sport, politics and the weather via our news app and get notifications sent straight to your smartphone.
